    <stitle>3300 HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - REMOVE - Grille</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Grille</title>
        <para>The grille and grille shroud assembly are a one-piece, painted, injection-molded assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0901021">Figure 31, Item 4</hotlnk>), designed with an aerodynamic styling to enhance the
            overall appearance of the 3300 PT series bus chassis.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0901021" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901021.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 31. Grille And Shroud Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. UPPER SHROUD MOUNTING TAB INSERT HOLES</callout1>
                <callout1>2. GRILLE / SHROUD SCREW MOUNTING TABS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. GRILLE / SHROUD MOUNTING SCREWS</callout1>
                <callout1>4. GRILLE / SHROUD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the four lower grille and shroud mounting screws on the grille assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0901021">Figure 31, Item 3</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the screws.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the grille assembly, lift the grille and shroud assembly out. Check the grille /
                shroud mounting tabs for damage after removal.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
